    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Just a Simple Taxi Ride</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Peter Lavigne letter says he would prefer reading lights to high-tech gadgets to be installed in New York City cabs (Jan 5 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''High-Tech Gadgets in Taxis Will Cut Profits, Cabbies Say'' (news article, Jan. 5):</p>
        <p>Touch-screen monitors that allow taxi passengers to watch television, get game scores and track their ride on a global positioning system?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''High-Tech Gadgets in Taxis Will Cut Profits, Cabbies Say'' (news article, Jan. 5):</p>
        <p>Touch-screen monitors that allow taxi passengers to watch television, get game scores and track their ride on a global positioning system?</p>
        <p>Not for me, thank you. I would be satisfied if New York taxis added one simple, inexpensive amenity: reading lights.</p>
        <p>Peter LaVigne  New York, Jan. 5, 2007</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
